    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Jackson Merrill** serving as our clear focal point; his elite score of 75.27 is bolstered by a leadoff spot against Sean Burke and a favorable 4.35 xERA matchup that perfectly complements his high sprint speed, which earns an additional boost due to the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** (70.65) and **Drake Baldwin** (67.34) anchor the lineup, as both benefit from superior matchup environments against Michael McGreevy and Brennan Bernardino, respectively. While **Gunnar Henderson** faces a tougher path against the lefty Weathers\u2014resulting in a significant 15% platoon penalty\u2014his role at the top of the order and the high probability of success on the basepaths against a slow-delivering pitcher keep his efficiency score viable at 55.17.\n\nStrategic benching was essential today, with **Coby Mayo** (52.17) standing as our most difficult omission. While **Coby Mayo** benefits from the same favorable game conditions as **Gunnar Henderson**, the optimizer prioritized the higher floor and defensive positional utility offered by the starting MI/3B group. Risk management remains critical, as several players\u2014including **Josh Jung**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Dominic Smith**\u2014are currently subject to \"Lineup Pending\" status; if **Josh Lowe** or **Dominic Smith** are shuffled into lower-leverage spots or scratched, we must be prepared to pivot to the bench. Furthermore, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** faces a stiff challenge against Prielipp, with a 16% SP skill penalty dragging his score down to 58.22; while he remains a start, his performance against this elite arm will be a key indicator of our overall offensive volatility today.",
